doc.after: In biology a phylum is a taxonomic rank below Kingdom and above Class Phylum is equivalent to the botanical term division The kingdom Animalia contains approximately forty phyla the kingdom Plantae contains twelve divisions Current research in phylogenetics is uncovering the relationships between phyla which are contained in larger clades like Ecdysozoa and Embryophyta The best known animal phyla are the Mollusca Porifera Cnidaria Platyhelminthes Nematoda Annelida Arthropoda Echinodermata and Chordata the phylum to which humans belong along with all other vertebrate species Although there are 36 animal phyla these nine include over 96 of animal species Many phyla are exclusively marine and only one phylum the Onychophora velvet worms is entirely absent from the world s oceans although ancestral onycophorans were marine
